The paper proposes a method for training directed latent variable models, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also mentions the use of feedforward networks and deep autoregressive networks, which are commonly used in computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions the use of the method on MNIST, which is a commonly used dataset in computer vision, suggesting the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a likely option. Finally, the paper also mentions achieving state-of-the-art results on the Reuters RCV1 document dataset, suggesting the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as a possible option.
